cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about learning continuous representations of discrete objects, which is a common problem in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. The paper proposes a Bayesian nonparametric prior for embeddings that encourages sparsity and leverages natural groupings among objects. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
